text: Umeå City Church () is a church building in the central parts of Umeå in Sweden. It is located between Vänortsparken and the northern bank of the Ume River. The church belongs to the Umeå City Parish of the Church of Sweden. It was inaugurated on 2 December 1894. That day was First Advent Sunday the same year year. ==References== ==Other websites== *Umeå stads kyrka Category:Church of Sweden churches Category:Umeå
